t often seen outside botanical gardens.","wiki"),("cress","5","___ , is a rather fast-growing, edible herb.","wiki"),("shiso","5","Perilla frutescens var. crispa, or ___ . Different parts of the plant have a number of culinary uses in East Asian and Southeast Asian cuisine.","wiki"),("chili","5","The ___ pepper , is the fruit of plants from the genus Capsicum which are members of the nightshade family, Solanaceae. ___ peppers are widely used in many cuisines as a spice to add heat to dishes. The substances giving ___ peppers their intensity when ingested or applied topically are capsaicin and related compounds known as capsaicinoids.","wiki"),("cubeb","5","Piper ___a, ___ or tailed pepper is a plant in genus Piper, cultivated for its fruit and essential oil. It is mostly grown in Java and Sumatra, hence sometimes called Java pepper. The fruits are gathered before they are ripe, and carefully dried. Commercial ___ consists of the dried berries, similar in appearance to black pepper, but with stalks attached – the 'tails' in 'tailed pepper'.  The dried pericarp is wrinkled, and its color ranges from grayish brown to black. The seed is hard, white and oily. The odor of ___ is described as agreeable and aromatic and the taste as pungent, acrid, slightly bitter and persistent.  It has been described as tasting like allspice, or like a cross between allspice and black pepper.","wiki"),("cumin","5","___  is a flowering plant in the family Apiaceae, native to southwestern Asia including the Middle East.","wiki"),("duqqa","5","___,","wiki"),("stump","5","After a tree has been cut and felled, the ___ or tree ___ is usually a small remaining portion of the trunk with the roots still in the ground. ___s may show the age-defining rings of a tree. The study of these rings is known as dendrochronology.","wiki"),("rumen","5","The ___, also known as a paunch, forms the larger part of the reticulo___, which is the first chamber in the alimentary canal of ruminant animals. It serves a